# --- Rust Specific ---
# The build directory where compiled binaries and libraries go
/target/

# --- IDEs / Editors ---
# VS Code
.vscode/
# IntelliJ / RustRover / PyCharm
.idea/
*.iml
# Vim / Emacs
*~
*.swp

# --- Environment & Secrets ---
# For local environment variables
.env
.env.*

# --- OS Specific ---
# macOS
.DS_Store
# Windows
Thumbs.db

# --- Locks ---
# Usually, you DO want Cargo.lock in your repo for a project/web-app 
# so others have the exact same dependency versions. 
# If this were a library meant for others to consume, you might ignore it.
# Cargo.lock